In the last six years, Czech Railways has invested over 31 billion crowns in the modernization of vehicles.
A third of the cars are currently equipped with air conditioning, roughly half of the trains have a new system of closed toilets.
The money spent resulted in a reduction of the average age by two years for locomotives and separate units and by six years for classic wagons.
