In 2014, they started preparing the Shippansee LTD application, which uses already planned trips between world capitals, mainly by plane, to transport packages.
In 2015, they assigned the project to a company that created applications for, for example, MALL.cz, Jobs.cz or ČSFD.
Programming took three quarters of a year and they launched the app in March 2016.
They started developing the Převeza application in December last year and released it in May this year.
This is a local version of Shippansee modified for the Czech market.
Mesíkem and Mesíkem Profi have been developing the application since January this year and made it available to users at the end of July 2016.
The intention from the beginning was to make all these applications that would one day merge into one.
In the Czech Republic, they want to fine-tune the application and then, in cooperation with a strong investor, focus more on the global market.
The sharing economy has been a topic lately and this is a service like AirBnB or Uber.
Aren&#39;t you worried about operating in an area about which no one can say much yet where the border of sharing is and where the gray economy is?
It&#39;s the same, just a different product.
It is clear to us that if it is successful and we go up with it, we will be the next thorn in the side of the gray economy.
But although someone saves and someone earns, it is not the intention to bypass the financial authorities and tax controls.
Every user, on one side or the other, will be encouraged to tax their income if they make income from it.
What makes you think that the service has such great potential?
The sender saves and the carrier earns or reduces the cost of the trip.
Therein lies the powerful idea that unites interest on both sides.
In the age of social networks that divide people, we would like this one to bring them closer together.
Nice stories can be created, people are happy to have helped someone and will tell each other about it.
Maybe someone will bring you forgotten glasses, keys or pills.
In my opinion, people have been missing a personal approach for a long time, we say about this application that it is a service of people to people.
So how do you guarantee that the courier doesn&#39;t run away with the package?
Each user of the application, together with the registration, scans the identity card and indicates the bank connection, payment or credit card.
These are the channels that give credibility to both the service and the person.
Couriers also collect stars based on sender ratings.
We will also offer insurance, we are still fine-tuning the details.
The courier is responsible for the uninsured shipment in case of loss or damage, but does not take responsibility under criminal law for the contents if there is something illegal inside and he does not know about it.
If the police stop him and find a machine gun or ten kilos of hashish in a sealed package in his suitcase, criminal responsibility falls on the sender.
Is there a risk of misuse of sensitive data from the database?
If necessary, the registrants can be traced by the administrative body, which will be the only one who will have the opportunity to look into it, even we ourselves are not able to see them, the data is protected against misuse.
How much money will the courier receive after successful delivery of the package?
The courier determines the price and gets the full amount he asks for.
The sender will be charged a few percent extra for arranging the contact.
This money is our profit, but it is only a few percent because we want to push the volume.
No one can blame the courier for not delivering the parcel, when he actually delivered it, both receipt and delivery are verified using QR codes.
Are there any restrictions?
Either in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can transport anything.
We have three sizes, small like a cube of butter, medium like a plate of eggs and large like a beer mug.
After that, there are no further restrictions and if someone has room in the car, they can transport, for example, a refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the app, so the courier can see what is wanted.
You don&#39;t even need to wrap the thing unless you really want to hide the contents.
You shove the forgotten sweatshirt into the courier&#39;s hand and that&#39;s it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to launch the service?
A friend got the idea more than two years ago, I didn&#39;t pay much attention to it then.
Then he showed me a demo of an app with a multinational reach that mainly targets air travelers.
At that moment I told him that I would not look for an investor, but I would like to become one myself and put my savings into it.
It took another year of development before we founded the Shippansee LTD company in London for greater credibility of the entire product.
But this isn&#39;t the version you&#39;re primarily focusing on right now.
No, we focused our marketing on the Czech Republic, where we are trying to catch up with the application, because the whole thing had birth pains and there is still something to solve and improve.
We are trying to respond to feedback from customers and we are not dealing with the foreign market that much at the moment.
We know it&#39;s a long shot, but we don&#39;t rush, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippansee LTD was the basic and most expensive app, the other two were upgrades of sorts.
Převež was created when we thought that the domestic segment could be much more interesting and that we would at least learn it in the Czech Republic.
The third application of Mesíkem is local, for the city.
But it can send a package to the exact address even to the other side of the world.
It works for the sender in the same way as Převeza, but the difference is that in it, as a courier, you can see shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator in your mobile phone.
We called the application for couriers who want to make a living Mesík Profi.
So can someone actually make extra money by picking up packages around town?
Exactly, the latest application will be downloaded in Prague by, for example, a taxi driver, a student, a mother on parental leave, someone who wants to save time on their way to work.
Now that everyone is fooling around with those pokemons, they might as well collect this.
A person can see where there are jobs around town, come to it, click and see when it has to be delivered and transport the shipment.
It&#39;s set up cheaper than competing services.
At the moment, we are still making a web interface, which will be crucial for companies sending shipments, they will fill in their information on the website, i.e. create points on the map.
We are then able to invoice them for the use of the service, for example, every month.
Are you working full-time on the project now?
It exhausts us, but we normally have it at work in order to sustain and develop the project.
There is no strong multinational investor hiding behind us, we are two guys, one of whom had a brilliant idea and the other jumped in with other stimuli and ideas.
We are now looking for an investor strong enough to manage not the Czech market with us, but who should go with us into a global product and become the next huge player in the market like AirBnB and Uber.
