The &quot;anime&quot; effect on Snapchat is criticized as an Asian caricature
According to Snapchat, the filter is inspired by anime, but some observers say it&#39;s racially insensitive.
Every day, Snapchat allows some 150 million users to alter reality and play with identity in ways that border on the absurd.
You can turn yourself into a pineapple, a dog, or a character that looks like it stepped out of a Roy Lichtenstein painting.
